ul.li:
Expensive operations in response to userland reconfigurations
	  now do not interfere with kernel filtering for more than the time
	  required to swap a pointer;

You can now use ports and the "tos" field as lookup argument
	  for tables.  This might allow some simplifications in rulesets which
	  in turn result in faster execution time;

ipfw can now send packets matching rules with a 'log' attribute
	  to the "ipfw0" pseudo interface, where you can run tcpdump to
	  implement additional filtering, logging etc.;
